A 42-year-old woman was arrested for manufacturing counterfeit money in Grassy Park, Western Cape police said on Thursday. Spokesperson Captain FC Van Wyk said at around 12.45pm on Wednesday, police attended to a complaint and found the woman making counterfeit money. The suspect was arrested with a printer and counterfeit money was confiscated. &#8220;The 42-year-old suspect is being detained on possession and manufacturing of counterfeit money. &#8220;She is due to appear in the in the Wynberg Magistrate s Court once charged, he said. African News Agency (ANA) ALSO READ: Jewellery store burgled inside Menlyn shopping centre For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.